6 Hot Cross Buns
40 g butter (softened)
1 packet cream
1 cup milk
2 egg
1 packet caster sugar

• Preheat oven to 200°C/180°C fan-forced.
• Slice hot cross buns into 1cm slices
• In a medium bowl, place cream, the milk, eggs and 1/2 the caster sugar.
Whisk until smooth.

• Arrange hot cross bun slices in a baking dish. Pour over cream mixture and
and allow to sit for 30 minutes.
• Meanwhile, in a small microwave-safe bowl, place the butter. Microwave in
10 second bursts until melted.

• Pour melted butter over pudding, then top with 1 tsp of remaining caster
sugar.
• Bake pudding until golden and custard is set, 40-45 minutes.

• Allow pudding to cool for 10 minutes.
• Divide hot cross bun pudding between bowls. Enjoy!